.FI
.SH "NOTES"
It is 
.B "not"
a good idea to run 
.I coin
on a 
.CT layer "cell map"
which has a monstrous number
of categories (such as unreclassed elevation).  
Because
.I coin
reports information for each and every category, it is better
to 
.I reclass[1] 
those categories into a more manageable number prior to running
.I coin
on the reclassed cell 
.CT "file." "map."

.I Coin
calculates the coincidence of two 
.CT "map layers," "cell maps."
.XT "one pair at a time."
Although
.I coin
allows the user to rerun the report using different units,
it is not possible to simply rerun the report with different 
.CT "layers." "cell maps."
In order to choose new 
.CT "layers," "cell maps,"
it is necessary to rerun
.I coin.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
cell.stats(1), report(1), Gdescribe(2G), Greport(2G), Gstats(2G)
.SH "AUTHORS"
Michael O'Shea, U.S. Army Construction Engineering Research Laboratory
